Sentencas: The reduced operating temperature is requisite for the wide application of the solid oxide fuel cells owing to the lower cost and longer lifetime.
Titulo: One-Dimensional CuCo2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Composite Fiber as Cathode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Nevertheless, in the intermediate temperature range, the significantly increased polarization loss appears in the solid oxide fuel cells, reducing the final performance.
Titulo: One-Dimensional CuCo2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Composite Fiber as Cathode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In order to solve this issue, here we report the one-dimensional CuCo2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 composite fibers, which are synthesized via electrospun method and utilized as cathodes of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: One-Dimensional CuCo2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Composite Fiber as Cathode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The optimal Er0.4Bi1.6O3 mass ratio of 35 wt % has been ascertained, possessing the lowest cathode polarization resistance of 0.021 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C, which is 3.3 times lower than those of the CuCo2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 nano particle-structured composite cathode.
Titulo: One-Dimensional CuCo2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Composite Fiber as Cathode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: All of the results demonstrate the potential of the CuCo2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 composite nanofiber serving as an efficient cathode for the intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: One-Dimensional CuCo2O4-Er0.4Bi1.6O3 Composite Fiber as Cathode of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
